  "doc_id": "10160",
  "text": "This also pertains to TAC concentrations, which in the study of Kilic et al. [CITATION_1] were significantly higher in the group of children with obesity compared with normal weight children. However, the authors demonstrated that increased TAC was the result of elevated TOC levels in an attempt to balance oxidation. They also suggest that the cause of greater TAC concentrations could be more active antioxidant systems in young people. However, reduced antioxidative activities in adults as well as children with obesity could be caused by considerable ROS production, which could be responsible for the depletion of antioxidant enzymes and a secondary reduction in the body's antioxidative capability. This seems to explain the observed increased as well as decreased TAC concentrations in people with obesity.",
